From Ken Hayashida Subject Long term Human Missions Mike Adams suggested discussions on long term effects of spaceflight to the human I love this topic as some of you regulars So having seen Henry's encouraging statement about starting to talk about it I I feel that we as a community of people have unique resources to deliver to the world a comprehensive book which can elaborate on the utility of spaceflight to fields which are as divergent as medical intensive care agriculture environmental protection and probably I do not believe that the general public understands the impact of spaceflight on the whole of In the absence of such knowledge we see dwindling support of the world's space I believe that we as a group have the responsibility to not only communicate amongst ourselves but also with others through print A well orchestrated and technically oriented analysis of life science variables required to support long duration spaceflight like long expenditions to the moon or Mars would be entertaining and educational to the general The objective of such an effort would be to compile resources and publications from accepted scientific and technical journals which would address each major life science In addition ideas for further research and development could be put forward for the general public to the general public to take part in the excitement of Individuals interested should be willing to devote an hour per week to running literature searches and finding journal In addition we need to obtain the assistance of personnel from within the halls of NASA and I have appreciated the positive responses to date and I am personally eager to start this Perhaps we could start with debate regarding how best to grade the viability of various technologies for application to ken